Order
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Let 
\begin_inset Formula $G$
\end_inset

 be a group.
 The 
\begin_inset Formula $\textbf{order}$
\end_inset

 of an element 
\begin_inset Formula $a\in G$
\end_inset

 is the least integer 
\begin_inset Formula $n\in\mathbb{N}$
\end_inset

 such that 
\begin_inset Formula $a^{n}=e$
\end_inset

.
 If no such integer exists, we say 
\begin_inset Formula $a$
\end_inset

 has infinite order.
 
\end_layout

