\begin_inset Formula $\{a^{n}\mid n\in\mathbb{N}\}$
\end_inset

.
 Since 
\begin_inset Formula $G$
\end_inset

 is finite, we must have 
\begin_inset Formula $a^{m}=a$
\end_inset

 for some 
\begin_inset Formula $m\in\mathbb{N}$
\end_inset

.
 This implies 
\begin_inset Formula $a^{m-1}=1$
\end_inset

.
